Leopard sharks (_Triakis semifasciata_) are found along the Pacific coast of North America, from the U.S. state of Oregon to Mazatl√°n in Mexico. The leopard shark is a temperate shark of both inshore and offshore continental littoral waters, generally found on or near the bottom in shallow water from the intertidal zone to 20 meters deep, although they have been found as deep as 156 meters. This species is generally found over soft bottom habitats and around rocky reefs and kelp forests. For a picture go to http://b.vimeocdn.com/ts/218/730/218730804_640.jpg. - Mod.PMB

